Definitions:

attempts 
    The number of iterations for which the query message is to be sent to the specified resource. (Defaults to 1.) 

target-path
    The RNS path to the GenesisII resource to be "pinged". 

query
    The character string to be echoed by the specified resource. 

Description:

The ping diagnostic tool sends a query-string to the specifed resource. If the user is authorized and the resource is available, the resource will echo the query-string back to the user. The round-trip exchange is attempted the specified number of times.

Code:

Implementing Class 
    edu.virginia.vcgr.genii.client.cmd.tools.PingTool 
